ftposium'%20academic%20summit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707753830000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F16870%2Fproduction%2F_132627229_swift-index-getty.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-australia-68271324%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20BBC%20goes%20inside%20the%20world's%20most%20dedicated%20effort%20to%20chart%20Taylor%20Swift's%20power%20and%20influence.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A33%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-australia-68271324%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-australia-68271324.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-australia-68271324.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nitish%20Wins%20Trust%20Vote%2C%20But%20Tejashwi%20Wins%20Hearts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30172607%2FF6h-A1CXQAAeurW.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatna%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Two%20weeks%20after%20returning%20to%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20fold%2C%20the%20Nitish%20Kumar-led%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA)%20government%20won%20the%20trust%20vote%20by%20129%3A0%20amidst%20the%20walkout%20from%20the%20Opposition%20in%20the%20Bihar%20Assembly%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20NDA%E2%80%99s%20no-confidence%20motion%20against%20Speaker%20Awadh%20Bihari%20Choudhary%20(Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal)%20was%20won%20by%20125%3A%20112%20votes%2C%20indicating%20amply%20that%20the%20ruling%20alliance%20had%20the%20numerical%20equations%20in%20its%20favour.%20The%20actual%20strength%20of%20the%20BJP-Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20and%20Hindustani%20Awam%20Morcha-Secular%20(HAMS)%20stands%20at%20128%20against%20114%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3EMahagadhbandhan%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0comprising%20the%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20(RJD)%2C%20Congress%20and%20the%20Left.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20RJD%20MLAs%2C%20including%20Chetan%20Anand%20and%20Neelam%20Devi%2C%20son%20and%20wife%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98gangsters%20turned%20politicians%E2%80%99%2C%20Anand%20Mohan%20and%20Anant%20Singh%20respectively%20crossed%20the%20floor%20to%20support%20the%20ruling%20alliance.%20It%20was%20understandable%20in%20the%20light%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20Nitish%2C%20of%20course%20with%20the%20support%20of%20the%20RJD%20(in%20the%20government%20then)%2C%20had%20changed%20the%20jail%20manual%20for%20the%20early%20release%20of%20Anand%20Mohan%2C%20a%20life%20convict%20in%20the%20IAS%20officer%20G.%20Krishnaiah%20murder%20case%20last%20year.%20Anant%20Singh%20stands%20convicted%20in%20multiple%20murder%20cases%20and%20is%20barred%20from%20contesting%20the%20polls.%20Neelam%20had%20contested%20the%20Mokama%20seat%20on%20behalf%20of%20her%20husband%20and%20won%20it%20in%202020%20polls.%20Observers%20said%20that%20it%20was%20hard%20for%20the%20MLAs%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Cwrong%20side%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20law%20to%20%E2%80%9Cantagonise%E2%80%9D%20the%20party%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20policemen%20in%20huge%20numbers%20patrolled%20around%20the%20house%20of%20the%20former%20deputy%20chief%20minister%2C%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%20who%20was%20with%20his%20party%20MLAs%20at%20about%202%20am%2C%20apparently%20to%20fuel%20fear%20among%20such%20MLAs.%20There%20were%20signs%20of%20fissures%20in%20the%20JDU%20too%20and%20Jitan%20Ram%20Manjhi%20(HAMS)%20with%20four%20MLAs%20had%20openly%20expressed%20his%20dissatisfaction%20against%20%E2%80%9Cpoor%20portfolio%20allocation%E2%80%9D%20to%20his%20MLA.%20The%20media%20was%20agog%20with%20the%20speculations%20of%20some%20JDU%20MLAs%20%E2%80%9Csnapping%E2%80%9D%20contact%20with%20Nitish%20Kumar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20these%20speculations%20were%20true%2C%20the%20RJD%2C%20Congress%20and%20Left%20were%20too%20poor%20to%20match%20the%20BJP%20in%20terms%20of%20%E2%80%9Cresources%E2%80%9D%20required%20in%20a%20power%20game.%20Armed%20with%20power%20at%20the%20Centre%2C%20financial%20muscle%2C%20overall%20control%20over%20the%20prosecuting%20agencies%20and%20penchant%20to%20selectively%20target%20the%20opponents%2C%20the%20BJP%20was%20better%20equipped%20to%20operate%20against%20the%20Opposition%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETejashwi%20Yadav%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%20Kumar-led%20NDA%20might%20have%20won%20the%20trust%20vote%20but%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%20has%2C%20apparently%2C%20won%20the%20heart.%20He%20sounded%20bitter%20when%20Nitish%20had%20dumped%20him%2C%20first%20time%2C%20in%202017.%20He%20used%20pungent%20words%20against%20Nitish%20then.%20His%20Monday%20speech%20was%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20that%20of%202017.%20With%20a%20smile%20on%20his%20face%2C%20Tejashwi%20began%20his%20speech%20by%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EAap%20(%3C%2Fem%3ENitish%3Cem%3E)%20meray%20aadarniya%20thay%2C%20aadarniyan%20hain%20or%20aur%20aadarniya%20rahengen%3C%2Fem%3E%20(I%20respected%20you%2C%20respect%20you%20and%20will%20keep%20on%20respecting%20you).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20dubbed%20me%20%E2%80%98beta%20(son)%E2%80%99.%20I%20honored%20you%20as%20an%20elder%20of%20the%20larger%20%E2%80%98Samajvadi%20parivar%E2%80%99%20and%20was%20obedient%20to%20you.%20But%20you%20have%20acted%20like%20king%20Dasratha%20who%20exiled%20his%20son%20Ram%20to%20the%20jungle%20under%20Kaikeyi%E2%80%99s%20pressure.%20I%20take%20it%20as%20an%20opportunity%20to%20go%20among%20the%20people%20and%20struggle%20for%20their%20rights.%20I%20will%20continue%20my%20battle%20against%20the%20dictatorial%20and%20anti-democratic%20forces%20the%20way%20my%20father%20(Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav)%20did%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tejashwi%20said%3B%20gravity%20was%20writ%20large%20on%20his%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20recalled%20that%20Nitish%20had%20laughed%20by%20saying%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Epaisa%20kahan%20se%20laayega%3C%2Fem%3E%20(where%20will%20he%20get%20money%20from)%E2%80%9D%2C%20when%20he%20(Tejashwi)%20promised%2010%20lakh%20jobs%20to%20the%20youths%20in%20the%202020%20assembly.%20%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20when%20you%20joined%20the%20%3Cem%3EMahagathbandhan%3C%2Fem%3E%20you%20began%20fulfilling%20my%20promise.%20I%20am%20happy%20that%20our%20Mahagathbandhan%20gave%20over%20four%20lakh%20jobs%20during%20a%20short-period%20of%20time%E2%80%94an%20unprecedented%20feat%20in%20the%20annals%20of%20India.%20The%20education%20department%20which%20was%20under%20the%20RJD%E2%80%99s%20quota%20alone%20handed%20out%20over%20two%20lakh%20jobs%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tejashwi%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%E2%80%9CNow%20you%20are%20accusing%20us%20of%20taking%20credit.%20Why%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20we%20take%20credit%20for%20the%20work%20we%20have%20done%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETejashwi%20reminded%20how%20Nitish%20had%20come%20back%20to%20the%20RJD%2C%20alleging%20openly%20that%20the%20BJP%20was%20all%20out%20to%20split%20his%20JDU.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20repeatedly%20alleged%20that%20they%20(BJP)%20had%20captured%20the%20media%20and%20the%20journalists%20were%20not%20publishing%20what%20you%20were%20saying.%20You%20repeatedly%20said%20that%20you%20would%20prefer%20to%20die%20than%20go%20back%20to%20the%20BJP%E2%80%A6I%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20repeat%20all%20these%20for%20they%20are%20too%20hackneyed%20now.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnimpressive%20Nitish%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgainst%20Tejashwi%E2%80%99s%20composure%2C%20Nitish%20looked%20bitter%20when%20he%20stood%20up%20to%20speak.%20He%20got%20angry%20when%20some%20opposition%20members%20tried%20to%20interrupt.%20The%20alacrity%20and%20flow%20he%20was%20once%20known%20for%20was%20missing.%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20was%20there%20in%20Bihar%20when%20I%20came%20to%20power%20in%202005%3F%20There%20were%20no%20roads%2C%20no%20electricity%2C%20no%20schools%2C%20no%20hospitals.%20The%20people%20feared%20coming%20out%20on%20the%20streets%20during%20the%20rule%20of%20your%20father%20(Lalu)%20and%20mother%20(Rabri%20Devi)%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20BJP%20members%20were%20seen%20smiling%20when%20Nitish%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CBarring%20a%20brief%20interregnum%20when%20I%20handed%20over%20the%20CM%E2%80%99s%20post%20to%20Jitan%20Ram%20Manjhi%2C%20I%20have%20been%20the%20CM%20for%2018%20years.%20I%20have%20stayed%20with%20the%20BJP%20for%20a%20large%20part%20of%20my%20stint%20as%20the%20CM%20and%20have%20carried%20out%20all-round%20development%20of%20the%20state.%20Now%2C%20I%20have%20come%20back%20to%20my%20old%20house.%20I%20won%E2%80%99t%20go%20anywhere%20from%20here%20now.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20downright%20wrong%20when%20he%20said%20that%20the%2015%20years%20of%20the%20Lalu-Rabri%20regime%20were%20infamous%20for%20riots%20between%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%20and%20he%20ensured%20justice%20for%20the%20minorities%20when%20he%20came%20to%20power%20in%202005.%20Lalu%20Yadav%20had%20come%20to%20power%20in%201990%20in%20the%20background%20of%20one%20of%20the%20worst-ever%20communal%20riots%20in%20Bhagalpur%20in%201989.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20anything%20Lalu%E2%80%99s%20rule%20is%20remembered%20for%2C%20it%20is%20for%20restoring%20the%20communal%20amity%20in%20Bihar.%20The%20only%20exception%20was%20the%20riot%20of%20Sitamarhi%20in%20the%201990s.%20Lalu%20had%20camped%20at%20Sitamarhi%20for%20seven%20days%2C%20moving%20out%20among%20the%20people%20to%20restore%20peace%20and%20carry%20out%20relief%20operations%20on%20a%20large%20scale%20which%20the%20then%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Chandra%20Shekhar%20had%20praised%20in%20glowing%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20Nitish%20initiated%20many%20measures%20to%20improve%20the%20condition%20of%20the%20minorities%20when%20he%20came%20to%20power%20in%202005%20in%20the%20era%20of%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%3B%20the%20BJP%20itself%20then%20was%20not%20as%20atrocious%20to%20the%20minorities%20as%20it%20is%20to%20Narendra%20Modi%20pursuing%20the%20radical%C2%A0Hindutva%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeedless%20to%20say%2C%20Nitish%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20able%20to%20protect%20minorities%20in%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20he%20did%20with%20Vajpayee%20at%20the%20helm%20of%20affairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20deputy%20to%20Nitish%2C%20Vijay%20Sinha%20heaped%20the%20charges%20of%20corruption%20on%20Lalu%20and%20his%20family%20and%20indicated%20that%20the%20investigating%20agencies%20would%20go%20hard%20on%20them.%20Nitish%2C%20who%20used%20to%20say%20that%20the%20investigating%20agencies%20were%20after%20the%20Lalu%20family%20because%20he%20had%20joined%20the%20Mahagathbandhan%2C%20sounded%20in%20tune%20with%20Sinha%20on%20Monday.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20were%20making%20money%20when%20they%20were%20in%20power%20with%20me.%20I%20will%20get%20the%20charges%20of%20corruption%20investigated%20now.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENalin%20Verma%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist%2C%20author%2C%20media%20educator%2C%20and%20independent%20researcher%20in%20folklore.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707749978000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30172607%2FF6h-A1CXQAAeurW.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnitish-kumar-may-have-won-trust-vote-but-tejashwi-yadav-emerges-as-real-victor%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Unlike%20Nitish%20Kumar%20who%20was%20bitter%20and%20unimpressive%20during%20his%20no-confidence%20motion%20speech%2C%20Tejashwi%20Yadav's%20composure%20with%20no%20inkling%20of%20ill-will%20won%20many%20hearts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnitish-kumar-may-have-won-trust-vote-but-tejashwi-yadav-emerges-as-real-victor%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Richard%20Branson%20suffers%20'nasty'%20injuries%20in%20cycling%20accident%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707749820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F02%2F768x432%2Fskynews-richard-branson-cycling_6453280.png%3F20240212153705%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Frichard-branson-suffers-nasty-injuries-in-cycling-accident-13070185%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sir%20Richard%20Branson%20has%20suffered%20%26quot%3Bnasty%26quot%3B%20injuries%20after%20hitting%20a%20pothole%20and%20falling%20off%20his%20bike%20in%20the%20British%20Virgin%20Islands%2C%20the%20billionaire%20has%20revealed%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A97%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Frichard-branson-suffers-nasty-injuries-in-cycling-accident-13070185%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IIT%20Professor%E2%80%99s%20Novel%20Technique%20Produces%20High-Quality%20Vermicompost%20in%20Half%20The%20Time%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EResearchers%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F333216%2Fiit-guwahati-invents-sensor-for-diabetes-diet-low-glycemic-index-food%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIIT-Guwahati%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20developed%20a%20novel%20two-stage%20biodegradation%20technique.%20This%20can%20not%20only%20help%20municipal%20corporations%20and%20other%20governing%20bodies%20to%20manage%20organic%20waste%20in%20an%20eco-friendly%20manner%2C%20but%20also%20generate%20quality%20vermicompost%20and%20organic%20compost%20with%20high%20NPK%20(nitrogen%2C%20phosphorus%2C%20and%20potassium)%20value%20and%20other%20micronutrients%20for%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELed%20by%20Dr%20Ajay%20S%20Kalamdhad%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20civil%20engineering%20at%20IIT-Guwahati%2C%20researchers%20under%20the%20institute%E2%80%99s%20Waste%20Management%20Research%20Group%20(WMRG)%20have%20devised%20an%20efficient%20and%20environmentally-friendly%20technique%2C%20which%20combines%20Rotary%20Drum%20Composting%20with%20Vermicomposting%20(RDVC).%20This%20novel%20technique%2C%20the%20institute%20claims%2C%20minimises%20biodegradation%20time%2C%20yields%20vermicompost%20with%204.2%25%20total%20nitrogen%20in%2027%20days%20(as%20compared%20to%20the%20standard%2045%20to%2060%20days)%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F339577%2Fhyderabad-abhishek-agarwal-goodeebag-free-waste-recycling-service%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eurban%20waste%20management%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20reduces%20the%20volume%20of%20waste%20by%2071%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20further%2C%20they%20also%20claim%20that%20this%20technique%20was%20also%20used%20to%20produce%20nutrient-rich%20soil%20conditioner%20(vermicompost)%20from%20invasive%20aquatic%20weeds%20like%20the%20water%20hyacinth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Mati%20Dhan%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20a%20high-quality%20organic%20vermicompost%20produced%20by%20the%20IIT%20Guwahati%20researchers%20by%20the%20novel%20two-stage%20biodegradation%20technique%20%E2%80%94%20is%20now%20available%20in%20the%20market%20and%20benefiting%20local%20farmers%2C%20according%20to%20Prof%20Kalamdhad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20institute%20transferred%20this%20technology%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farcus-www.amazon.in%2FOrganic-Vermicompost-Fertilizer-Manure-Plants%2Fdp%2FB091Q83KGD%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThis%2520compost%2520will%2520be%2520rich%2Cand%2520small%252Dscale%2520organic%2520farming.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAMER%20Private%20Ltd%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20startup%20incubated%20at%20IIT-Guwahati%2C%20which%20is%20now%20manufacturing%20%3Cem%3EMati%20Dhan%20Organic%20Vermicompost%20Fertilizer%20Manure%20for%20Plants%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20available%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farcus-www.amazon.in%2FOrganic-Vermicompost-Fertilizer-Manure-Plants%2Fdp%2FB091Q83KGD%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThis%2520compost%2520will%2520be%2520rich%2Cand%2520small%252Dscale%2520organic%2520farming.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20other%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiamart.com%2Fapshishtmanagement-environmentalresearch%2Fagriculture-vermicompost.html%2323268501673%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonline%20marketplaces%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EStudying%20waste%20management%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20Professor%20Kalamdhad%20talks%20about%20dedicating%20his%20career%20to%20solid%20waste%20management.%20During%20his%20tenure%20as%20a%20professor%2C%20he%20has%20worked%20with%20many%20PhD%20students%20addressing%20a%20diverse%20range%20of%20issues%20related%20to%20solid%20waste%20management%20in%20the%20Indian%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20major%20sets%20of%20projects%20which%20stand%20out%20according%20to%20him%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1)%20Studying%20different%20techniques%20of%20composting%20of%20water%20hyacinth%20(a%20freshwater%20weed)%20given%20its%20ubiquitous%20presence%20in%20aquatic%20ecosystems%20all%20over%20Northeast%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2)%20Pilot-scale%20studies%20on%20rotary%20drum%20composting%20and%20anaerobic%20bi-phased%20baffled%20reactor%20(aka%20ABBR%2C%20which%20digests%20any%20kind%20of%20biomass)%20technology%20for%20the%20biomethanation%20(a%20process%20by%20which%20organic%20material%20is%20converted%20under%20anaerobic%20conditions%20to%20biogas)%20of%20industrial%20sludge%20and%20aquatic%20weeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20these%20projects%20received%20funding%20from%20the%20Science%20and%20Engineering%20Research%20Board%20(SERB)%20under%20the%20Department%20of%20Science%20and%20Technology%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Science%20and%20Technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20initially%20found%20that%20in%20the%20rotary%20drum%20composting%20process%2C%20accountable%20degradation%20was%20observed%20in%20the%20first%20seven%20days%20followed%20by%20the%20cooling%20phase%20of%20compost%20materials.%20These%20studies%20were%20all%20conducted%20in%20a%20batch%20scale%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Professor%20Kalamdhad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFurther%20we%20had%20also%20worked%20on%20vermicomposting%20using%20various%20worm%20cultures%20where%20we%20observed%20that%20%3Cem%3EEisenia%20fetida%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20species%20of%20earthworm)%20was%20robust%20in%20degrading%20diverse%20organic%20wastes%20including%20weed%20biomass.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20the%20results%20demonstrated%20that%20the%20vermicomposting%20process%20was%20effective%20not%20from%20day%201%20but%20from%20day%2010%20to%2015%20depending%20on%20the%20type%20of%20feed.%20The%20idea%20of%20replacing%20the%20initial%20period%20of%20the%20vermicomposting%20with%20rotary%20drum%20composting%20was%20thought%20of%20and%20studies%20were%20conducted%20accordingly%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20effort%20resulted%20in%20the%20development%20of%20the%20two-stage%20biodegradation%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Earthworms-1707743947.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Earthworms%20used%20by%20researchers%20at%20IIT%20for%20vermicompost%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Earthworms-1707743947.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Earthworms-1707743947-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Earthworms-1707743947-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Earthworms-1707743947-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Earthworms-1707743947-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-341531%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EEarthworms%20used%20for%20vermicomposting%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHow%20does%20this%20work%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOrganic%20material%20often%20makes%20up%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20municipal%20solid%20waste%20deposited%20in%20open%20dumpsites%20across%20different%20Indian%20cities%2C%20generating%20a%20lot%20of%20heat%20due%20to%20long-term%20decomposition.%20This%20poses%20serious%20environmental%20challenges%20in%20the%20long%20term.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20comparison%20to%20other%20waste%20biodegradation%20techniques%2C%20which%20require%20two%20to%20three%20months%2C%20rotary%20drum%20composting%20(RDC)%20can%20convert%20%E2%80%9Cdiverse%20organic%20feedstocks%20into%20nutrient-dense%20compost%20within%20just%2020%20days%20and%20significantly%20reduce%20the%20municipal%20waste%20volume%20by%2060%20to%2070%25%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20a%20recent%20press%20release%20issued%20by%20the%20institute.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20said%20that%2C%20RDC%20is%20known%20to%20generate%20compost%20of%20%E2%80%9Cmoderate%20quality%20as%20compared%20to%20vermicompost%20%E2%80%9D.%20Vermicomposting%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20is%20a%20superior%20biodegradation%20process%2C%20which%20requires%20anywhere%20between%2045%20to%2060%20days.%20Given%20the%20time%20frame%20required%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F171989%2Fmadhya-pradesh-ias-indore-municipal-commissioner%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emunicipal%20corporations%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecan%E2%80%99t%20employ%20it%20on%20a%20large%20scale.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20WMRG%20under%20Professor%20Kalamdhad%20developed%20a%20unique%20two-stage%20biodegradation%20technique%20which%20combines%20the%20best%20of%20RDC%20and%20vermicomposting%20to%20reduce%20the%20duration%20of%20biodegradation.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20earthworms%2C%20%3Cem%3EEisenia%20fetida%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20can%20acclimatise%20faster%20to%20partially%20degraded%20organic%20matter%20from%20the%20drum%20compost%20and%20produce%20vermicompost%20in%20just%2027%20days%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20product%20was%20proven%20to%20be%20non-toxic%20and%20safe%20to%20be%20used%20as%20a%20nutrient-rich%20soil%20conditioner%20(vermicompost)%20from%20waste%20with%204.2%25%20total%20nitrogen.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Preparing-the-Substrate--1707744030.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Preparing%20substrate%20for%20vermicomposting%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Preparing-the-Substrate--1707744030.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Preparing-the-Substrate--1707744030-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Preparing-the-Substrate--1707744030-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Preparing-the-Substrate--1707744030-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Preparing-the-Substrate--1707744030-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-341532%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EResearchers%20engaged%20in%20substrate%20preparation%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20The%20Better%20India%2C%20Professor%20Kalamdhad%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20developed%20technique%20combines%20the%20thermophilic%20biodegradation%20of%20RDC%20and%20mesophilic%20biodegradation%20of%20vermicompost.%20The%20RDC%20time%20was%20studied%20to%20be%20seven%20days%2C%20and%20the%20requirement%20of%20vermicomposting%20was%2020%20days.%20We%20studied%20the%20response%20of%20the%20diverse%20organic%20waste%20with%20the%20technique%20before%20arriving%20at%20a%20conclusion.%20To%20explain%20in%20layman%E2%80%99s%20terms%2C%20if%20you%20use%20RDC%20before%20vermicomposting%2C%20it%20helps%20vermiculture%20(earthworms)%20stabilise%20the%20organic%20waste%20faster.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20employed%20all%20the%20possible%20biomasses%20for%20the%20study%2C%20majorly%20including%20vegetable%20waste%2C%20aquatic%20weeds%2C%20terrestrial%20weeds%20and%20sewage%20sludge.%20The%20experimental%20verification%20of%20this%20combined%20technique%20was%20conducted%20both%20in%20the%20laboratory%20and%20on%20a%20large%20scale%20at%20the%20Solid%20Waste%20Laboratory%20of%20IIT%20Guwahati.%20A%205%2C000-litre%20RDC%20unit%20and%20a%203%2C000-litre%20stack%20vermicomposting%20unit%20were%20established%20to%20study%20the%20large-scale%20effect%20of%20the%20process%2C%20with%20the%20moisture%20content%20controlled%20using%20horticulture%20waste%20collected%20on%20campus%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHelping%20him%20verify%20this%20technique%20is%20PhD%20student%20Mr.%20Suryateja%20Pottipati%2C%20who%20experimentally%20proved%20the%20hypothesis.%20They%20published%20the%20results%20in%20reputed%20international%20academic%20journals%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20Journal%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0956053X22001611%3Fvia%253Dihub%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBiomass%20Conversion%20and%20Biorefinery%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0301479722017625%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJournal%20of%20Environmental%20Management%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0960852421016990%3Fvia%253Dihub%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBioresource%20Technology%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0956053X22001611%3Fvia%253Dihub%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWaste%20Management%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201373px)%20100vw%2C%201373px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FRVDC-method-1707743840.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221373%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Vermicompost%20making%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FRVDC-method-1707743840.jpg%201373w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FRVDC-method-1707743840-300x167.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FRVDC-method-1707743840-500x279.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FRVDC-method-1707743840-768x428.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FRVDC-method-1707743840-150x84.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-341530%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22766%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20RVDC%20method%20established%20by%20Professor%20Kalamdhad%20and%20his%20team%20at%20IIT-Guwahati%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECan%20Municipal%20Corporations%20use%20this%20new%20technique%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20press%20release%20issued%20by%20the%20institute%2C%20Professor%20Ajay%20Kalamdhad%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20proven%20technique%20not%20only%20handles%20sizable%20quantities%20of%20organic%20waste%20but%20also%20offers%20immediate%20application%20feasibility%20for%20municipal%20corporations%2C%20industries%2C%20sewage%20treatment%20facilities%2C%20aquatic%20weeds%20and%20various%20organic%20waste%20management%20sectors.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20release%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20scaled-up%20process%20successfully%20produced%20100%20to%20150%20kg%20of%20vermicompost%20within%20a%20month%20from%20250%20to%20300%20kg%20of%20daily%20waste%20fed.%20The%20increased%20earthworm%20count%20resulted%20in%20the%20secondary%20end%20product%20being%20the%20earthworm%20itself.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20he%20explains%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20study%20included%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F332396%2Fhow-to-make-bio-enzymes-from-kitchen-waste-at-home-diy-steps-by-kolkata-gardener-nita-singh%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evegetable%20waste%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20aquatic%20weed%20(water%20hyacinth)%20as%20prime%20substrates%2C%20both%20in%20mono-substrate%20composting%20and%20co-composting.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20entire%20study%2C%20we%20have%20converted%2015%20tonnes%20of%20waste%20collected%20from%20the%20markets%20and%20ponds%20around%20the%20IIT%20Guwahati%20campus%20(350%20kg%20per%20day).%20The%20confidence%20that%20we%20gained%20through%20the%20study%20is%20the%20basis%20on%20which%20we%20are%20suggesting%20that%20the%20technology%20can%20handle%20sizable%20quantities.%20We%20believe%20this%20process%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20reshape%20organic%20waste%20treatment%20facilities%20globally%2C%20providing%20an%20environmentally%20compatible%20solution%20to%20mitigate%20contamination%20hazards%20and%20produce%20an%20outstanding%20soil%20conditioner%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Edited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3B%20Images%20courtesy%20IIT-Guwahati)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707746351000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D341515%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dr%20Ajay%20S%20Kalamdhad%20led%20a%20group%20of%20IIT-Guwahati%20researchers%20to%20innovate%20a%20two-stage%20fast%20biodegradation%20technique%20that%20can%20aid%20municipal%20corporations%20in%20eco-friendly%20organic%20waste%20management.%20It%20also%20produces%20%E2%80%98Mati%20Dhan%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20a%20top-notch%20vermicompost%20and%20organic%20compost%20rich%20in%20NPK%20and%20other%20essential%20nutrients%20for%20farmers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Rinchen%20Norbu%20Wangchuk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Egypt's%20ominous%20threat%20to%20suspend%20peace%20deal%20should%20be%20taken%20seriously%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707745800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F02%2F70x70%2Fskynews-rafah-gaza-israel_6452660.jpg%3F20240212070914%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fegypts-ominous-threat-to-suspend-peace-deal-over-rafah-offensive-should-be-taken-seriously-by-israel-13070103%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Israel's%20worst-ever%20security%20disaster%20happened%20on%20prime%20minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu's%20watch%20on%20October%207.%20He%20may%20now%20preside%20over%20one%20of%20the%20most%20grave%20diplomatic%20setbacks%20in%20its%20history.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A270%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fegypts-ominous-threat-to-suspend-peace-deal-over-rafah-offensive-should-be-taken-seriously-by-israel-13070103%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fegypts-ominous-threat-to-suspend-peace-deal-over-rafah-offensive-should-be-taken-seriously-by-israel-13070103%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fegypts-ominous-threat-to-suspend-peace-deal-over-rafah-offensive-should-be-taken-seriously-by-israel-13070103%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mosque%2C%20Temple%20and%20the%20'Neutrality'%20of%20Indian%20Institutions%3A%20Reflections%20of%20an%20Ordinary%20Muslim%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F27153406%2Fbabri_masjid-11302_2486082a-e1563521469520.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2Fp%2Fbharat-ratna-as-modis-key-election%5C%22%3Epiece%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0was%20first%20published%20on%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20India%20Cable%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%93%C2%A0a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%C2%A0The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3Eclick%20here%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%20in%20a%20Muslim%20family%20in%20Lucknow%2C%20I%20often%20heard%20accounts%20of%20the%20demolition%20of%20Babri%20mosque%20on%20December%206%2C%201992%2C%20which%20Hindutva%20leaders%20claimed%20as%20the%20birthplace%20of%20Lord%20Rama.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20they%20had%20asserted%20that%20the%20Mughal%20king%2C%20Babar%2C%20had%20built%20a%20mosque%20after%20destroying%20a%20Rama%20temple.%20Even%20as%20a%20child%2C%20I%20could%20sense%20a%20deep%20discomfort%20and%20anxiety%20amongst%20my%20Muslim%20friends%20and%20family%20members%20on%20the%20mosque%20question.%20The%20demolition%20of%20the%20mosque%20had%20a%20profound%20impact%20on%20their%20social%2C%20political%20and%20cultural%20outlook.%20I%20inherited%20that%20anxiety%20as%20I%20grew%20up%20mostly%20surrounded%20by%20my%20Muslim%20family.%20The%20accounts%20and%20narratives%20of%20my%20family%20members%20made%20me%20feel%20a%20range%20of%20emotions.%20I%20vividly%20remember%20asking%20my%20father%20about%20the%20December%201992%20incident%20and%20what%20he%20felt%20when%20the%20mob%20demolished%20the%20mosque.%20My%20childhood%20self%20was%20petrified%20and%20frustrated%20with%20the%20imagination%20of%20a%20group%20of%20Hindutva%20leaders%20leading%20a%20mob%20in%20broad%20daylight%20to%20demolishing%20the%20disputed%20structure%2C%20signifying%20a%20vulgar%20display%20of%20majoritarianism.%20In%20hindsight%2C%20I%20would%20read%20my%20question%20as%20an%20inquiry%20about%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20ideals%20on%20which%20this%20state%20was%20built%20by%20its%20makers%20%E2%80%93%20democracy%2C%20secularism%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20father%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20my%20questions%20was%20based%20on%20developments%20at%20the%20time.%20He%20told%20me%20that%20in%201992%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party-led%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20government%20had%20submitted%20an%20affidavit%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20pledging%20to%20safeguard%20the%20disputed%20structure%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Babri%20mosque.%20Like%20many%20ordinary%20Indians%2C%20he%20believed%20that%20the%20government%20would%20honour%20its%20commitment%20made%20before%20the%20highest%20court%20in%20the%20country.%20As%20a%20child%2C%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20response%20satisfied%20my%20curiosity%20and%20generated%20an%20impression%20that%20a%20%E2%80%98neutral%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98impartial%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98apolitical%E2%80%99%20judiciary%20was%20tricked%20by%20a%20cunning%20and%20majoritarian%20government.%20Muslims%2C%20like%20my%20father%2C%20had%20no%20complaints%20with%20the%20judicial%20process%20but%20with%20how%20the%20promises%20made%20before%20the%20judiciary%20were%20broken%20by%20a%20%E2%80%98rogue%E2%80%99%20government.%20If%20the%20%E2%80%98neutral%E2%80%99%20judiciary%20had%20its%20day%2C%20it%20would%20have%20checked%20the%20Hindutva%20forces%20from%20creating%20mayhem.%20I%20grew%20up%20internalising%20this%20narrative%20of%20the%20judiciary%20as%20a%20saviour%20in%20the%20face%20of%20majoritarianism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20late%2C%20I%20have%20been%20thinking%20about%20the%20conversations%20I%20had%20with%20my%20father%20back%20then.%20I%20often%20wonder%20how%20I%20would%20respond%20if%20future%20generations%20posed%20a%20similar%20question%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20developments%20of%20the%20last%20few%20years.%20I%20have%20probably%20come%20to%20the%20realisation%20that%20when%20the%20conversation%20with%20the%20past%20fails%20to%20satisfy%20us%2C%20perhaps%20it%E2%80%99s%20best%20for%20our%20sanity%20to%20have%20a%20conversation%20with%20the%20future.%20That%20is%20where%20the%20revolutionary%20potential%20lies%20%E2%80%94%20or%20at%20least%20the%20hope%20for%20it.%20The%20developments%20over%20the%20last%2010%20years%20have%20reshaped%20my%20imagination%20in%20the%20light%20of%20the%20rise%20of%20aggressive%20Hindutva%20politics%20during%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20rule%20in%20India%20since%202014%2C%20especially%20given%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20in%20November%202019%20granting%20the%20land%20on%20which%20Babri%20mosque%20stood%20before%20December%201992%20to%20the%20Hindu%20claimants%2C%20and%20more%20recently%2C%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20Rama%20temple%20on%20that%20land%20and%20the%20vulgar%20display%20of%20religious%20supremacy%20surrounding%20the%20%3Cem%3EPran%20Pratishtha%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20present-day%20India%2C%20as%20I%20reflect%20on%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20answers%2C%20the%20vision%20of%20the%20judiciary%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98saviour%E2%80%99%20and%20a%20check%20to%20majoritarian%20oppression%20no%20longer%20holds%20merit.%20It%20is%20evident%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20unanimous%20judgment%20allocating%20the%20land%20to%20those%20who%20had%20demolished%20the%20Babri%20Mosque%20ended%20up%20legitimising%20the%20destruction%20of%20the%20mosque.%20This%20judgment%20has%20emboldened%20Hindutva%20supremacist%20groups%2C%20fostering%20demands%20for%20the%20conversion%20of%20other%20mosques%20in%20India%20into%20temples%2C%20thereby%20leading%20to%20incidents%20reminiscent%20of%20the%20Babri%20demolition.%20The%20Babri%20judgement%20serves%20as%20a%20microcosm%20of%20institutional%20neglect%20of%20Muslims%2C%20including%20by%20the%20judiciary%20which%20has%20created%20the%20grounds%20for%20the%20continuous%20reproduction%20and%20strengthening%20of%20majoritarian%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%2C%20we%20now%20will%20have%20a%20different%20answer%20to%20offer%20to%20our%20future%20generation.%20This%20articulation%20will%20differ%20from%20facile%20explanations%20of%20the%20current%20situation%20which%20look%20at%20the%20present%20times%20as%20an%20aberration%20to%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20democratic%20history.%20Rather%2C%20we%20will%20perhaps%20better%20understand%20the%20postcolonial%20Indian%20state%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98majoritarian%E2%80%99%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3EMinorities%20and%20the%20Making%20of%20Postcolonial%20States%20in%20International%20Law%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EMohammad%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EShahabuddin%20has%20argued%20that%20the%20foundation%20of%20post-colonial%20nation%20states%20rests%20on%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20uniform%20national%20identity%20that%20assimilates%20all%20ethno-cultural%20distinctions.%20Despite%20the%20envisioned%20outcome%20of%20assimilation%20and%20homogenisation%20eradicating%20minority%20issues%20in%20the%20long%20term%2C%20the%20actual%20process%20tends%20to%20diminish%20meaningful%20ethno-cultural%20diversity.%20Instead%2C%20it%20reduces%20this%20diversity%20to%20a%20mere%20token%20representation%2C%20imposing%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20majority%20on%20the%20entire%20nation.%20In%20the%20name%20of%20nation-building%20and%20homogenization%2C%20the%20culture%2C%20belief%20system%20and%20cultural%20codes%20of%20the%20majority%20become%20synonymous%20with%20the%20%E2%80%98national%E2%80%99%20identity.%20Contrary%20to%20the%20belief%20that%20the%20minority%20problem%20gets%20resolved%20in%20a%20liberal%20and%20developmental%20state%2C%20the%20postcolonial%20national%20state%20has%20effectively%20served%20as%20a%20tool%20to%20perpetuate%20the%20dominance%20of%20the%20majority%20group%20over%20the%20minority%20across%20political%20and%20cultural%20spheres%2C%20leaving%20the%20minority%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20majority%E2%80%99s%20influence%20on%20crucial%20political%2C%20social%20and%20economic%20matters.%20This%20phenomenon%20is%20not%20exclusive%20to%20India%3B%20similar%20patterns%20can%20be%20observed%20in%20other%20post-colonial%20states%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20the%20deliberations%20within%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20clearly%20demonstrate%20the%20%E2%80%98majoritarian%E2%80%99%20nation%20making%20at%20play%20while%20addressing%20the%20concerns%20associated%20with%20minority%20communities.%20Dr.%20BR%20Ambedkar%2C%20chairperson%20of%20the%20drafting%20committee%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20advocated%20reservations%20to%20minorities%2C%20specifically%20in%20the%20cabinet%20in%20proportion%20to%20their%20population.%20This%20proposal%20was%20presented%20by%20Ambedkar%20in%20his%20memorandum%20titled%20%E2%80%98States%20and%20Minorities%E2%80%99%20and%20submitted%20it%20to%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20in%201946.%20However%2C%20the%20assembly%20rejected%20this%20suggestion%20in%20the%20name%20of%20national%20unity.%20In%20post-partition%20India%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20minority%20representation%20was%20considered%20counterproductive%2C%20linked%20to%20the%20division%20of%20the%20country.%20Despite%20demands%20for%20robust%20and%20meaningful%20safeguards%20for%20minorities%2C%20nationalist%20elites%20rejected%20them%2C%20emphasizing%20the%20goal%20of%20building%20%E2%80%98One%20Nation%E2%80%99.%20Thus%2C%20the%20Advisory%20Committee%20abandoned%20reservations%20for%20religious%20minorities%2C%20leaving%20their%20protection%20to%20the%20majority%E2%80%99s%20goodwill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Hindu%20nationalists%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20sought%20a%20constitutional%20ban%20on%20cow%20slaughter%2C%20linking%20it%20to%20Hindu%20religious%20sentiments%2C%20Muslim%20members%20highlighted%20the%20inconsistency%20within%20the%20prevailing%20liberal%20secular%20rhetoric%20in%20the%20assembly%2C%20which%20was%20unwilling%20to%20accommodate%20the%20concerns%20of%20religious%20minorities.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20the%20assembly%20included%20a%20directive%20principle%20prohibiting%20cow%20slaughter%20in%20the%20Constitution%2C%20blending%20religious%20sentiments%20with%20cultural%20and%20economic%20considerations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prevalence%20of%20majoritarian%20views%20in%20the%20constituent%20assembly%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20minority%20rights%20tells%20us%20that%20post-colonial%20India%20was%20%E2%80%98conceived%E2%80%99%20as%20a%20majoritarian%20state.%20It%20should%20not%20surprise%20us%20that%20the%20judiciary%20too%20became%20an%20arena%20where%20these%20pro-majoritarian%20values%20got%20reinforced.%20In%20fact%2C%20judicial%20pronouncements%20signal%20an%20end%20to%20political%20discourse%20because%20the%20judiciary%20has%20the%20ability%20to%20speak%20the%20final%20word.%20By%20taking%20matters%20to%20the%20judiciary%2C%20we%20limit%20the%20scope%20and%20chances%20of%20political%20resolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20India%20is%20witnessing%20brute%20Hindutva%20majoritarianism%2C%20the%20rhetoric%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98neutrality%E2%80%99%20of%20institutions%20stands%20exposed.%20It%20is%20for%20everyone%20to%20see%20how%20putative%20%E2%80%98democratic%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98neutral%E2%80%99%20institutions%20have%20given%20way%20to%20power.%20The%20fact%20is%20that%20the%20terms%20of%20%E2%80%98neutrality%E2%80%99%20were%20fixed%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20making%20of%20the%20constitution.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20our%20institutions%20are%20%E2%80%98neutral%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20what%20constitutes%20%E2%80%98neutrality%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98fairness%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98non-arbitrariness%E2%80%99%20was%20circumscribed%20by%20majoritarianism.%20The%20present%20times%20are%20no%20aberration.%20The%20exclusion%20of%20minorities%20was%20well-entrenched%20in%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20author%20is%20Assistant%20Professor%2C%20Dr.%20Ram%20Manohar%20Lohiya%20National%20Law%20University%2C%20Lucknow.%C2%A0%20He%20thanks%20Haris%20Jamil%20and%20Priya%20Anuragini%20for%20their%20comments.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707745233000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F27153406%2Fbabri_masjid-11302_2486082a-e1563521469520.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmosque-temple-and-the-neutrality-of-indian-institutions-reflections-of-an-ordinary-muslim%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20a%20time%20when%20India%20is%20witnessing%20brute%20Hindutva%20majoritarianism%2C%20the%20rhetoric%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98neutrality%E2%80%99%20of%20institutions%20stands%20exposed.%20It%20is%20for%20everyone%20to%20see%20how%20putative%20%E2%80%98democratic%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98neutral%E2%80%99%20institutions%20have%20given%20way%20to%20power.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmosque-temple-a