20process%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Vaibhav%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aim%20is%20to%20mimic%20the%20climes%20of%20the%20Valley%2C%20as%20the%20seeds%20only%20flower%20at%20a%20specific%20temperature.%20Elaborating%20on%20how%20they%20managed%20to%20achieve%20this%2C%20Vaibhav%20says%20%E2%80%9CThe%20temperature%20in%20the%20room%20has%20to%20be%20decreased%20gradually%20just%20as%20if%20winter%20is%20coming%20to%20Kashmir.%20We%E2%80%99re%20essentially%20trying%20to%20make%20the%20seeds%20feel%20at%20home.%20So%2C%20we%20start%20at%2025%20degrees%20Celsius%20and%20gradually%20drop%20the%20temperature%20to%20five%20degrees%20through%20the%20next%20four%20months%20until%20harvest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStep%204%3A%20Pluck%20the%20flowers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20purple%20bloom%20conveys%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F276908%2Fdehradun-gardener-flower-plants-how-to-garden-youtube%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20harvest%20is%20ready%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Each%20flower%20comprises%20petals%2C%20the%20stamen%20and%20the%20stigma.%20%E2%80%9CEach%20of%20these%20parts%20has%20a%20different%20use.%20The%20petals%20are%20used%20in%20the%20cosmetic%20industry%2C%20the%20yellow%20stamen%20is%20used%20in%20the%20textile%20industry%20for%20dyeing%2C%20and%20the%20stigma%20is%20the%20red%20saffron.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStep%205%3A%20Place%20the%20seeds%20back%20into%20the%20soil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COnce%20the%20flowers%20have%20been%20plucked%20out%2C%20all%20the%20seeds%20are%20placed%20back%20into%20the%20soil%20so%20they%20can%20flower%20again%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Vaibhav%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20cycle%20that%20began%20on%2015%20August%20was%20completed%20on%201%20November%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEnsure%20that%20you%20water%20the%20seeds%20every%207%20to%2010%20days%2C%20and%20not%20exceed%20this%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20informs.%20Once%20it%E2%80%99s%20August%2C%20the%20flowers%20will%20be%20harvested%20again.%20%E2%80%9CThus%2C%20you%20see%2C%20each%20bulb%20has%20a%20lifetime%20of%20a%20decade%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F17686%2F5-secrets-to-the-most-amazing-terrace-garden-from-expert-viswanath-kadur%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrowing%20saffron%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20one-time%20investment.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhy%20history%20loves%20this%20%E2%80%98red%20gold%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20there%20is%20one%20spice%20that%20is%20history%E2%80%99s%20favourite%2C%20it%20has%20to%20be%20saffron.%20Legends%20tell%20of%20how%20Cleopatra%20bathed%20with%20it%20and%20Alexander%20the%20Great%20used%20it%20to%20heal%20battle%20wounds.%20Price%20is%20no%20bar%20it%20seems%20as%20some%20traders%20in%20Kashmir%20get%20a%20handsome%20Rs%202%20lakh%20per%20kg%20according%20to%20an%20article%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20article%20sheds%20light%20on%20how%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20expensive%20spice%E2%80%9D%20is%20not%20every%20country%E2%80%99s%20cup%20of%20tea.%20Iran%20produces%2095%20percent%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20saffron%20and%20Kashmir%20a%20great%20margin%20too.%20The%20spice%E2%80%99s%20demand%20for%20a%20certain%20climate%20means%20not%20every%20country%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F332547%2Fsooraj-purushothaman-organic-farmer-kerala-gardening-growing-vegetables%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efavourable%20for%20growth%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20it%20takes%20one%20lakh%20flowers%20to%20produce%20one%20kg%20of%20saffron%20(and%20the%20entire%20process%20must%20be%20done%20by%20hand)%20adds%20to%20it